About this program:

Wb96 Changed name to Excalibur

This version is based on WB96 Beta 14, the last version I made I think is beta 16 or beta 18, that version how ever is lost in my Amiga Disk collection and featured launch programs from start bar,

This version of Excalibur 2005 edition, is improved by removing file limit, and it uses real icons in the menu,  the start menu uses the system for opening files as Workbench, so you do not need to configure any datatype system,
the startbar features screen tabs for quick and easy access to programs running on other screens. 

( The start menu do not yet support drag & drop, auto-close / auto-select menu is not featured, and I think it's annoying windows features ;-) and are going to be dally by other plans. )

for more information have a look at @{"done" link DONE } 

@endnode

@node "DONE" "Done"

@{b}Done@{ub}

V0.9.6

* Bug fix, all windows closed if you pressed on the right edge of the start bar, this ended in a crash.
* Improved the look of the screen tab
* The screen buttons are now only drawn when need to reduce CPU load
* Screen tab bitmaps are freed when not used
* Menu lister position bug fixed
* Screen buttons use the fills out remaining area if clock is switched off
* LockPubScreeen() where never unlocked, so wb where unable to switch resolution.

V0.9.5

* Added Gfx memory status bar
* Exchange support added (not done)
* Fixed memory update bug, when bar is small
* Fixed the info text placement for memory bars
* Truncate long file names
* Display and select screen from task bar
* Open drawers from start menu whit a double click
* More colors on memory status bars (if you like)
* Quick_Install script

V0.9

* Cleaned up some code
* "Quit & About" added even if menuprefs is not loaded!
* Spelling error in the guide
* FAQ added
* Prefs program fixed
* View icons on/off
* select menu logo
* ReadConfig() cleanup, using human readable values

*	playing whit the cLose windows on menu select the
	program started crashing like hell so I added,
	some error checking, if program faills to open window!!

* Bugs are getting squashed
* Bar size = Small / Large 
* removed printf()'s

V0.8

* Converted BlitzBasic syntaxes to C syntaxes (all lines)
* Changed from sub routines to functions
* Created a bunch of fake blitz basic commands
* Moved tables in to structures
* Rewritten configure load routines big time
* Removed max files limit in start menus (dynamic table)
* Added data structure for files
* CursX() replaced by TextLength().
* Disabled some non working code for now.
* Memory status bar look fix
* InsMem() func removed (it looks 99% likes Memory func )
* Removed title-bar form windows
* Added Mouse-Move event, fixed event routine
* fixed Memory status bars 
* Display time 
* Removed Bar3D() and fixed some gfx problems
* Mouse on window check added (mouse move event is not needed)
* Fixed menu system
* Text Height check
* In the file ReadConfig() found problem reading stack value, due to my quick port, it's now fixed
* Execute files using wbrun command
* Load and render icons
* Center fonts & Icons in menu item
* Load logo using datatypes system
* Open next sub menu, y pos fixed to last selected item in previous menu
* Removed ProgID() file type checking, it's done by AmigaOS now
* Added support for progs in menu
* Removed Icon/blitz shape number info from Excaliburmenu.prefs / ReadConfig()
* fixed the time.device, so now the program do not opendevice() for every second, annoying in snoopdos!

@endnode

