@node "Install" "Install"

 just copy envarc/Excalibur dir to envarc:

 edit the envarc:Excalibur/ExcaliburMenu.prefs

 MENU TEXT =F,FILENAME
 MENU TEXT =D,PATH

 D=DIR, F=FILE

 copy envarc:Excalibur to env:

when you have done that, use ExcaliburPrefs to tune it for your needs.

(if you have wb96 installed, delete envarc:wb96)

@endnode

@node "FAQ" "FAQ"

 Q: The prefs program stops working when using / saving prefs
 A: Remove HappyEnv (MountEnv) from user-startup / startup-sequence

 Q: <FAB> How can I keep the output window from displaying?
 A: Run it from user-startup, (I'm going to remove the output text)

	run  >nil: Excalibur-2005-edition >nil:

 Q: <FAB> Can I choose alternate icons to be used instead of the WB icons?
 A: No, I think about scaling the Icons, 

 Q: <FAB> Can I get the various screens that are open to be shown in the start bar?
 A: It's done 

 Q: <FAB> Can I make Excalibur hide itself until the mouse is brought down to the bottom of the screen?
 A: The original beta 18 or so did, I'm going to add this, when I don't know, (when it's done).

@endnode
